<p><b>What is the minimum population required for gram panchayat in Maharashtra?</b> A gram panchayat can be set up in villages with a population of more than five hundred. There is a common gram panchayat for two or more villages if the population of these villages is less than five hundred, whereupon it is called a group-gram panchayat.</p>
